Text.Value: Who says you have to feel anything?
Don't thank me - I'm breaking Lady Shar's teachings just by doing so... but sometimes you have to be practical.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little embarassed at being thanked

Text.Value: Fumble in my head again and I'll gut you.
I know that. I had just hoped you might show some more understanding. Leave me alone, please.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: SH approval of player greater than 10
EditorData.NodeContext: A little wounded by the player's brusque 'pull yourself together' advice

Text.Value: You're a Shar worshipper, aren't you?
I didn't agree to join up with a Shar worshipper.
I can't trust you. Best if we travel separately for now.
It's nothing, I swear.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: SH approval of player is greater than zero, less than ten
EditorData.logicalname: APPROVAL GREATER THAN ZERO, LESS THAN TEN

Text.Value: Something's wrong. I feel... I feel...
No... or at least, I don't think so. Perhaps Lady Shar is testing me somehow. But if she is, then I have no idea what her purpose is.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: SH approval of player greater than 10
EditorData.NodeContext: Troubled speculation. She doesn't understand the strange magic afflicting her.

Text.Value: Let's see how open-minded I can be then: tell me more.
I... yes, she must. I'll offer thanks to her in my prayers - and we should speak more later. Alone, ideally.
Don't make a fuss, Sel√ªnite - we may be at odds, but I have more important concerns than you right now.
It's nothing. Even if it was something, I'm clearly not going to tell you, am I? Let it go.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: SH approval of player is less than zero

Text.Value: Don't be sorry - just tell me what you're hiding.
'Darkness protect me'? What did you mean by that?
I don't need your tough love. I need to be left alone. Now.
In future, I expect you to be honest. Let's leave it at that for now.
Talk to me later. The day's been long enough already.
True. I didn't think you'd react so pragmatically. Perhaps I should have told you sooner.
I... it's difficult for me to talk about. I'm sorry.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: SH approval of player is greater than 10

Text.Value: Gather your thoughts. Then, perhaps, we can talk some more.
...and stop looking at me like that. I'm not sprouting tentacles just yet.
Don't worry. Whatever it is, we're in this together.
You worship Shar? Blimey. She and my beloved Mystra are not exactly friends.
I'm fine. It's passed, whatever it was...
A lie of omission at most. I'm sure you have some skeletons of your own hidden away.
We can discuss this later. But let's just try a little more honesty going forward.
Now that the truth's out, tell me more.
*Uncertainty. Shadowheart is wrestling with what this pain means. Perhaps it is connected to Shar, she wonders, or perhaps not...*
What was that all about?
Use your shared connection. Enter her thoughts.
Fantastic. Monsters in our minds, and around our campfire.

EditorData.NodeContext: muttering angrily - just found out one of her companions worships an evil goddess

Text.Value: Use your shared connection. Enter her thoughts.
Never you mind.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: SH approval of player is less than zero

Text.Value: I'm not sorry I kept this from you. Not one bit.
Though perhaps that might change, if you can show an open mind.

EditorData.NodeContext: Conceding jus a little towards the player's hurt feelings - but conditionally

Text.Value: I worship Shar, the Mistress of the Night.
Please, it's nothing. Just let it rest.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: SH approval of player is greater than zero

Text.Value: You're not going to let this go, are you?
Forever, ideally. And you assume too much about what I can and cannot tell.
Gladly.
I don't care who you worship. We have bigger problems.
Your blindness as much as my deception, Sel√ªnite. We can talk about this later - if you're willing.
Now that you have the truth, please don't make a big fuss about it.
Of course I am. But we can talk about this later - I want to enjoy the still of the night.
Turn a blind eye and leave.
You could have told me. How long were you going to keep this secret?
...I should have been more discreet around you, clearly. Yes, you're right.
I don't know how I feel about this.
Then it's your own fault for not asking.
Not some sort of Sharran magic...?
The goddess of secrets? How telling.
I... thank you. But I'm sure it was nothing. I just... need a little space.

EditorData.NodeContext: Tiny bit of gratitude while still trying to dismiss the topic.

Text.Value: Are you hurt?
Don't make a big fuss...? You've been lying to me!
Change the subject.
Pull yourself together. We've all got fears to wrestle with.
*You sense her trying to understand what just happened. She silently begs her goddess for guidance - Shar.*
Stop! If I want to tell you something, I'll use my mouth - understand?
Shar is an abomination. You deceived me.
If you insist. Don't expect to fare well without me to save you.
I said I don't know. Forget it.
I'll decide whether to make a fuss or not. Hard to trust someone who's holding out on me.
Heavens forbid. We're all entitled to our secrets.
No... I'm fine. Forget it.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little shaken, but trying to brush it off.

Text.Value: I bow to Shar also. The Dark Lady must favour us, to have brought us together.
Could it be her tadpole? Ask how she feels.
I... I don't know.
A Shar worshipper? Not my usual quarry - nor my usual ally.
It's been some time since I met another faithful of Shar. Are you versed in her teachings?
All we can do is try, I suppose...
There's more to this. What aren't you telling me?
Secrecy is everything for Shar's children. It's our code, our creed, our shield.
Thank you for telling me, at least.
Ngh, it hurts... Darkness protect me...

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Shadowheart reacts to the pain of the incurable wound in her right hand. She raises the hand and grimaces in pain. After a brief moment the pain passes and she lowers her hand, face relaxing, returning to default pose.

Text.Value: Leave.

Synopsis: At camp, Shadowheart experiences a brief flare-up of mysterious magical energy, She reacts with alarm an utters the name of Shar, her patron goddess. If other party members are present, they ask her what just happened.
